  "texts": [
    "The principle of the IBISbased agent is simple: By classifying the types of existing posts, the agent generates facilitation messages according to the types of them to promote participants.",
    "For example, encouraging participants to give their ideas about an issue or to evaluate existing ideas, etc.",
    "Definition of Inclusive Discussion EnvironmentAs we pointed out as the first issue, in discussion environments without human facilitators, it is harder for shy participants to join in discussions while it is easier for some dominant participants to lead the discussion at their own pace.",
    "A survey figuring out the factors affecting the participation rates in class discussions shows that student traits such as confidence or comprehension, and discussion environment elements like interaction norms, are the two important factors [8].",
    "Therefore, by quoting the definition of inclusion in work groups, which means that different diverse individuals could blend into the environment safely and harmoniously [9], [10], the discussion environments with the IBIS-based agent cannot say \"inclusive\" enough."
